{
  "texts": [
    "The RNN model stands out as the most consistent high performer, but particularly for Malaysia, with an impressive R2 score of 0.9897, dwarfing the already high score of 0.96 for the UAE.",
    "The MAE for Malaysia was 0.002, which is only marginally higher than that for the UAE (0.0017).",
    "Therefore, for sheer performance and consistency, the RNN model is unsurpassed by Malaysian data.",
    "MLP presents a unique case where the R2 score for Malaysia is misleadingly high at 0.99827 despite a skyrocketing MAE of 3058.42, indicating some issues perhaps related to overfitting or metric calculations.",
    "In contrast, for the UAE, the high R2 score of 0.98 is marred by an equally anomalous MAE of 1075."
  ]
}